{"title_page": "Schomberg Municipality", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name = Schomberg\n| other_name = Gemeinde Schomberg\n| image_skyline =\n| imagesize =\n| settlement_type = [[Municipalities of Germany|Gemeinde]]\n| total_type = Total\n| image_flag =\n| image_shield =\n| image_map =\n| subdivision_type = Country\n| subdivision_name = \n\n* [[File:Flag of the German Empire.svg|20px]] [[German Empire]] (to 1918)\n* [[File:Flag of Germany (3-2 aspect ratio).svg|20px]] [[Weimar Republic|German Reich]] (1918-1933)\n* [[File:Flag of Germany (1935\u20131945).svg|20px]] [[Nazi Germany|German Reich]] (1933-1945)\n| subdivision_type1 = [[Provinces of Prussia|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Province of Silesia|Silesia]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[Districts of Germany|Rural District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Bytom|Beuthen District]]\n| leader_title = \n| leader_name = \n| area_total_km2 = \n| population_total = 7464| population_as_of = 1939\n| population_density_km2 =\n| population_urban = \n| population_blank1_title =\n| population_blank =\n| coor_pinpoint = Szombierki\n| coordinates = {{coord|50|20|0|N|18|53|0|E|region:PL|display=inline,title}}\n| seat = [[Szombierki|Schomberg]]\n| website =\n}}\n\n'''Gemeinde Schomberg''' ([[Upper_Silesia#Ethnolinguistic_structure_before_the_plebiscite|Polish]]: ''Gmina Szombierki''), was a [[Municipalities of Germany|municipality]] in the [[Bytom|District of Beuthen]], part of the [[Province of Silesia|Silesian Province]] of Germany. Its seat was the town of [[Szombierki|Schomberg]] (now a district of [[Bytom]]).\n\n==History==\nDuring the [[Upper Silesian plebiscite]] in 1921, 3328 people in the Schomberg municipality took part in the voting.\n\nResults<ref>Wyniki plebiscytu na G\u00f3rnym \u015al\u0105sku. Dziewulski, Stefan. ''p. 12-13''. http://polona.pl/item/67859822</ref><ref>http://www.historycy.org/index.php?showtopic=14864&st=17</ref>:\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!&nbsp; ||colspan=2|Votes for Germany||colspan=3|Votes for Poland||colspan=4|Emigrants||colspan=5|Total Votes||colspan=6|Total Population of municipality\n|-\n|Municipality/Gemeinde||colspan=2|'''702'''||colspan=3|'''1996'''||colspan=4|110||colspan=5|2698||colspan=6|4832\n|-\n|Estate Area/Gutsbezirk||colspan=2|'''244'''||colspan=3|'''371'''||colspan=4|16||colspan=5|615||colspan=6|1167\n|-\n|}\nEven though the majority of Schomberg's residents voted to join Poland, the city remained under German rule after the plebiscite era.\n\nIn 1930 the municipality became the owner of the [[Fazaniec (Bytom)|Fazaniec Park]].\n\nThe municipality of Schomberg ceased to exist in 1945 following the [[Territorial changes of Poland immediately after World War II|Polish takeover of Silesia]]. Under the new Polish administration a new [[Gmina|municipality]] (Gmina) was formed in Schomberg and the town's name was changed to Chruszcz\u00f3w.\n\n==Demographics==\nPopulation of the municipality (Gemeinde) of Schomberg<ref>https://treemagic.org/rademacher/www.verwaltungsgeschichte.de/beuthen.html</ref>:\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!&nbsp; ||colspan=2| Population\n|-\n|''Year'' || ''Number''\n|-\n|1905 || '''3837'''\n|-\n|1910 || '''4832'''\n|-\n|1919 || '''5549'''\n|-\n|1933 || '''8081'''\n|-\n|1939 || '''7446''' \n|-\n|}\nNationality (according to the German census of 1910)<ref>Wyniki plebiscytu na G\u00f3rnym \u015al\u0105sku. Dziewulski, Stefan. ''p. 12-13''. http://polona.pl/item/67859822</ref>:\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!&nbsp; ||colspan=2|German||colspan=3|%||colspan=4|Polish||colspan=5|%||colspan=6|Total Population||colspan=7|%\n|-\n|Municipality/Gemeinde||colspan=2|'''841'''||colspan=3|17.4%||colspan=4|'''3770'''||colspan=5|78%||colspan=6|'''4832'''||colspan=7|100%\n|-\n|Estate Area/Gutsbezirk||colspan=2|'''393'''||colspan=3|33.7%||colspan=4|'''624'''||colspan=5|53.5%||colspan=6|'''1167'''||colspan=7|100%\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Old Town Hall, Szombierki]]\n\n{{Navbox\n|name  = Beuthen Rural District\n|state={{{state|uncollapsed}}}